           2.1 THE NERVOUS SYSTEM \
\
All behavior (e.g., movement, thought, sleep) results from activity in the cells of the \
nervous system. The nervous system has two main divisions: a) the central nervous system \
(CNS), which consists of the brain and spinal cord; and b) the peripheral nervous system \
(PNS), which consists of the nerves that go to and from the brain and spinal cord (i.e., the \
cranial nerves, spinal nerves and peripheral ganglia). \
\
Below is an outline of the organization of the nervous system. This is followed by detailed \
descriptions of each area. \
\
