B. THE PEPTIDE NEUROTRANSMITTERS \
\
There are dozens of peptide neurotransmitters, consisting of long chains of amino acids. \
Two of them, the enkephalins and endorphins, also known as the endogenous opioids, \
help to regulate stress and pain. Another peptide, Substance P, is also involved in pain \
regulation. \
