(together) and aithesis (perception). Synesthesia runs in families and occurs in people who \
are neurologically normal. Current estimates are that 1 in 2,000 to 1 in 25,000 have \
synesthesia. Famous examples include the novelist Vladimir Nabokov and the artist David \
Hockney. \
