\
>ANXIETY DISORDERS Although benzodiazepines are effective in treating anxiety, \
 because of their high potential for abuse and dependence, they should generally be \
 prescribed for short periods of time. When patients complain of anxiety, it is important to \
 first consider possible underlying causes of their symptoms. Medical illness (e.g., \
 hyperthyroidism, stroke, myocardial infarction, asthma, peptic ulcer disease), illicit drugs \
 (e.g., cocaine, amphetamine), or withdrawal from CNS depressants (e.g., benzodiazepines, \
 alcohol), may trigger anxiety. \
\
     PANIC DISORDER Xanax (alprazolam) and Ativan (lorazepam) are helpful for \
     panic disorder. The SSRIs or tricyclic antidepressants are usually the drug of choice \
     for treating panic disorder on a longer-term basis. \
\
