                    3.2 PREAMBLE \
\
The Preamble states that the goals of the Ethics Code are "the welfare and protection of the \
individuals and groups with whom psychologists work," as well as "the education of \
members, students, and the public regarding ethical standards of the discipline." The \
preamble makes several other points: \
\
        Psychologists work toward increasing scientific and professional knowledge of \
        behavior and people's understanding of themselves. \
        The goal of psychologists is to improve the condition of individuals, \
        organizations, and society. \
        Psychologists respect and protect civil and human rights and the principles of \
        freedom of inquiry and expression. \
        Psychologists engage in a variety of roles, such as researcher, educator, \
        diagnostician, therapist, supervisor, consultant, administrator, social \
        interventionist, and expert witness. \
        Psychologists make a personal commitment to act ethically; they encourage the \
        ethical behavior of others; and they consult with others regarding ethical \
        problems. \
\
\
\
