greater access to their records, as well as increased understanding of how their records will \
be used. What follows are six basic patients' rights. \
\
     RIGHT OF NOTICE Patients have the right to be informed about the \
     psychologist's privacy policy and the ways in which personal health information \
     may be used or disclosed, as well as patients' rights to limit uses and disclosures. \
     Patients should be provided with a written copy of the psychologist's privacy \
     policy. \
\
