I. LEGAL ISSUES \
\
Industrial/Organizational psychology is affected by several legal issues or acts. \
\
>TITLE VII OF THE CIVIL RIGHTS ACT OF 1964 Title VII is the original Equal \
Employment Opportunity (EEO) Act. It states that one cannot discriminate on the basis of \
sex, ethnicity, and a variety of other factors. \
\
>UNIFORM GUIDELINES ON EMPLOYEE SELECTION    In 1978, the Equal \
Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) created the Uniform Guidelines on \
Employee Selection. According to these guidelines, the use of any test that adversely \
affects hiring, promotion, or other selection procedures, constitutes discrimination. The use \
of such a test may still be acceptable, however, if the test is validated, has utility, and no \
alternatives are available. \
\
>AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT The Americans with Disabilities Act \
(1990) bans discrimination in employment, transportation, access to public buildings, as \
well as discrimination in other settings. It also requires that companies make reasonable \
accommodations for disabled individuals. \
\
A "qualified individual with disability" is one who can perform the essential functions of \
the employment position with or without reasonable accommodation. "Reasonable \
accommodation" is defined as making existing facilities readily accessible to and usable \
by individuals with disabilities, and includes such things as job restructuring, modified \
work schedules, adjustment or modification of exams, and acquisition or modification of \
equipment. \
\
\
\
