similarity between the training situation (e.g., concepts covered, the skills learned) and the \
actual work situation. \
\
>FEEDBACK People learn best with feedback. Feedback should be offered as soon as \
possible. Training is better when the program allows for frequent feedback. \
\
>REINFORCEMENT   Reinforcement affects the speed of learning. The greater the \
reward, the more rapidly the behavior will be learned. Initially, continuous (and immediate) \
reinforcement should be given; later on, the schedule can be thinned. \
