relatedness needs as compared to men. \
\
>MCCLELLAND'S ACQUIRED NEEDS THEORY    McClelland's Acquired Needs \
Theory (1950s) resulted from MeClelland's experimenting with the Thematic \
Apperception Test (TAT) to measure needs. He went on to describe three significant work- \
related needs. \
\
     nACH nAch, the need for achievement, is the desire to do something better, solve \
