E. JOB-RELATED FACTORS \
\
In addition to personal factors, job-related factors affect motivation and satisfaction. An \
example of a job-related factor is the particular approach the company takes towards its \
employees. \
\
>HUMAN FACTORS APPROACH The human factors approach, contrary to what the \
name sounds like, is concerned with physical aspects of the job. Time and motion studies \
address ways to maximize speed and minimize wasted movement. The focus is on the \
"operator-machine system," how humans and machines work together to accomplish a job. \
\
>THE PSYCHOLOGICAL APPROACH    The psychological approach to job design \
assumes that efficiency and effectiveness are correlated with satisfaction, and that \
