OD interventions are targeted at a variety of levels. Strategies at the organization-wide \
level include survey feedback, confrontation meetings, structural redesign, collateral \
organization, and MBO. At the group level, interventions include team building, process \
consultation, and intergroup team building. At the individual level, elements include \
sensitivity training, management training, role negotiation, job redesign, and career \
planning. Research has found OD interventions difficult to evaluate. Overall, the most \
robust finding is that the more rigorous the research, the smaller the effect is. \
\
