Therapy requires that the client agree to the following four conditions: to work in therapy \
for a specified period (typically one year) and within reason to attend all sessions; if \
suicidal behavior is present, to work on reducing this; to work on any behaviors that \
interfere with the course of therapy (therapy-interfering behaviors); and to attend skills \
training. \
