\
C. TREATMENT AND TECHNIQUES \
\
The focus in classical analysis is on making the unconscious conscious, specifically, \
bringing to light the conflicts between the id's impulses that are pressing for discharge, and \
the efforts to repress these impulses by the ego defenses. \
\
The cornerstone of psychoanalysis is free association. The process of treatment includes \
four steps: clarification, confrontation, interpretation, and working through. The analysis \
of dreams is also a significant aspect of treatment, Transference and countertransference \
are important in analytic work, with transference (both negative and positive) seen as a \
form of resistance that must be worked through. \
\
\
 \
\
