\
reframe the depressive symptoms as a response to sex roles, sexism, or the oppressive \
socio-political climate. \
\
Feminist therapists strive for an egalitarian relationship with their clients and make \
appropriate self-disclosing statements about their own experiences of overcoming \
oppression and striving for autonomy; therefore, they serve as role models for their clients. \
In addition, feminist therapists can be distinguished from nonsexist therapists by the fact \
that feminist therapists advocate for socio-political change. \
\
V. PROCHASKA'S TRANSTHEORETICAL MODEL OF \
BEHAVIOR CHANGE \
\
According to the Transtheoretical Model of Behavior Change, people progress through a \
series of stages when making changes in their behavior. This model has been used in the \
treatment of addictive behaviors such as smoking and drinking, eating disorders, and \
weight management, and has also been used to promote health-related behaviors. The five \
stages of change in this model are: precontemplation, contemplation, preparation, action. \
and maintenance. \
\
>PRECONTEMPLATION In the precontemplation stage, individuals do not believe \
they have a problem. Typically, defenses have been constructed that aid in denial of the \
problem. There is no intention to change behavior during this stage. \
\
>CONTEMPLATION In the contemplation stage, individuals begin to acknowledge \
having a problem and may increase awareness and knowledge related to the problem. The \
contemplation stage is marked by ambivalence. During this stage, no attempts to change \
are made, nor is there even a commitment to change. \
\
>PREPARATION In this stage individuals have developed a commitment to change and \
begin to construct a detailed plan for change. By the time they reach this stage, individuals \
begin to perceive greater benefits than barriers to change. \
\
>ACTION During this stage, behavior change is initiated. Others are likely to recognize \
a person's progress toward change. After at least six months in the action stage, the person \
may move into the fifth and final stage. \
\
>MAINTENANCE   In the final stage of maintenance, individuals take steps to prevent \
relapse and to maintain the gains made during the action stage. \
\
\
