>CONSULTEE-CENTERED ADMINISTRATIVE CONSULTATION In this type of \
 consultation, the consultant focuses on the consultee's difficulties that limit effectiveness \
in instituting program change. For example, a consultant meets with a therapist who works \
in psychosocial rehabilitation in order to increase the therapist's knowledge about this type \
of program with the goal that the program be implemented more effectively. \
