 II. PREVENTION \
\
Prevention is a significant part of community psychology. The three levels of prevention \
are primary, secondary, and tertiary. \
\
>PRIMARY PREVENTION    Primary prevention attempts to prevent the onset or \
occurrence of a disease or disorder, and thereby reduce its incidence (or the number of new \
cases). Frequently, primary prevention focuses on building psychological health through \
