\
Overall, children whose parents divorce seem to adjust better than children who to live \
with parents in a state of ongoing marital conflict. Children of divorce do better when the \
custodial parent provides a stable, structured, nurturing environment, and does not have \
unrealistic, age-inappropriate expectations of the children. To facilitate recovery, parents \
should control their anger, cooperate in parenting, and avoid arguing in front of the \
children. \
\
Initially, girls seem to adjust better than boys do; however, girls become increasingly \
vulnerable in adolescence and if the mother remarries. The most difficult relationship in \
blended families is between stepmothers and stepdaughters. \
\
Meta-analytic research reviewing 37 studies and involving 81,000 people (Amato & Keith, \
1991) found that, compared to adults who grew up in intact families, adult children of \
divorced parents tend to have higher levels of depression and marital problems and lower \
levels of SES and health. \
\
