between power and beta: Power = 1 - beta. Thus, beta has the most significant and \
measurable effect on power. Power and alpha have a direct relationship. As alpha increases. \
so does power. \
\
>CORRECT DECISION WITH NO NAME    A final possibility is that the null is \
accepted, and this decision turns out to be correct. In other words, significance is not found \
in the original experiment, and subsequent researchers also do not find significance. There \
is no name for the decision when the null is correctly accepted. \
