>TYPES OF CORRELATIONS AND VARIABLES \
\
     ZERO-ORDER CORRELATION This is the most basic correlation. A zero- \
     order correlation analyzes the relationship between X and Y when it is believed that \
     there are no extraneous variables affecting the relationship. \
\
     PARTIAL CORRELATION (FIRST ORDER CORRELATION) A partial \
     correlation examines the relationship between the predictor and the criterion with \
     the effect of a third variable removed. The third variable is removed because it is \
