In path analysis, straight arrows denote causal relationships and are called paths. Curved \
arrows denote correlational relationships. Variables are described as either exogenous or \
endogenous. Models can be either recursive or non-recursive. Estimates of the causal \
relationships among variables are called path coefficients, and are determined by a series \
of multiple regression equations. Path coefficients are analyzed to see if the pattern \
