C. DEVELOPMENT OF A PREDICTOR TEST \
\
There are a variety of steps that are typically taken in order to develop a predictor test. \
\
>CONCEPTUALIZATION   In the first phase, conceptualization, the test developer \
decides on the test's objective, administration, and overall format (e.g., this will be a 20- \
item test designed to predict sales potential). \
\
>TEST CONSTRUCTION During the test construction stage, the developer decides on \
item format (e.g., multiple choice, T/F) and writes the items. Keep in mind that if the goal \
is ultimately to have a 20-item test, many more than 20 items will need to be developed \
(e.g., 50 or so). \
\
