\
     ITEM DISCRIMINATION Item discrimination looks at how well a particular \
     item discriminates between high scorers and low scorers. \
\
     ITEM VALIDITY Item validity is simply the correlation between item score and \
     criterion score. The higher the correlation, the more valid the item is. \
\
     THE ITEM-CHARACTERISTIC CURVE The item characteristic curve is a \
     plot of the relationship between item performance and total score. Item difficulty \
     level is defined as the 50% threshold, i.e., the score at which respondents have a \
     fifty-fifty chance of getting the given item right. The mathematical approach \
     involved in plotting and analyzing item-characteristic curves is called item response \
     theory (IRT) or latent trait theory. \
