>RELIABILITY OF THE PREDICTOR The reliability of the predictor test affects \
criterion-related validity. A test cannot be valid unless there is some degree of reliability. \
A reliable test, however, does not imply that there will be any validity whatsoever. In other \
words, reliability sets a ceiling on validity. Mathematically, the relationship between \
reliability and validity is expressed as: \
