construct is a hypothetical concept that typically cannot be measured directly, e.g., \
motivation, fear, or aggression. Evidence of construct validity can be ascertained in a \
variety of ways, the most common of which are factor analysis (see Statistics section), or \
the multi-trait, multi-method matrix. \
\
The multi-trait, multi-method matrix is a table with information about convergent and \
