A significant trend in the behavioral sciences is toward a biopsychosocial understanding of \
clinical phenomena. Theories of psychological development and functioning increasingly \
emphasize the interpersonal nature of psychological functioning, interpersonal \
interactions, and the person-environment relationship. Social psychology is concerned with \
