>THE SELF-SERVING (HEDONIC) BIAS The self-serving bias (Bradley, 1978) \
proposes that when we explain our own behavior, we tend to attribute our own successes \
to internal or personal factors, and our failures to external or situational factors. It is thought \
that this bias is motivated by a desire to maintain self-esteem as well as to look good to \
others. \
