members at headquarters in Hawaii to discuss whether they should prepare for possible \
attack by Japan. The admiral and his advisors, who shared similar backgrounds and \
perspectives, discounted many warnings of imminent attack and continued with business \
as usual. Thus, they were completely unprepared for the devastating attack on Pearl Harbor. \
\
 C. TASK PERFORMANCE \
\
Research on the effects of groups on task behavior has found mixed results. Three \
phenomena have been described, including social facilitation, social inhibition, and social \
loafing. \
\
>SOCIAL FACILITATION Social facilitation occurs when individual task performance \
is enhanced by the mere presence of others. Social facilitation occurs most frequently when \
the task is simple or familiar. \
\
 >SOCIAL INHIBITION Social inhibition occurs when task performance is \
compromised by the presence of others. Social inhibition occurs when the task is novel or \
complex. \
\
>SOCIAL LOAFING Social loafing refers to the phenomenon that people don't work as \
hard on a task when they are part of group as compared to when they are working alone. \
Social loafing most frequently occurs when people perceive that their individual efforts \
will be anonymous and thus not subject to individual evaluation. \
