   D. NATIVE AMERICANS/ALASKA NATIVES \
\
   Currently, only 20% of Native Americans live on reservations or trust lands. The poverty \
   rate among all Native Americans is twice that of the general population. Native Americans \
   traditionally have a general world view that emphasizes connectedness, balance, and \
   completeness. \
\
   >MENTAL HEALTH ISSUES The suicide rate for Native Americans is 1.5 times the \
   national rate, and is especially high among males ages 15 to 24. Fetal Alcohol Syndrome \
   and alcohol-related deaths are more common among Native Americans than the general \
   population. Higher rates of PTSD stem from a rate of violent victimization that is more \
   than twice the national average. \
\
   There is a long tradition of healing rituals among Native Americans who make no \
   distinction between mental and physical illness. Alternative medicine practices are utilized \
   at a rate equal to or greater than that of Whites. \
\
   >IMPLICATIONS FOR TREATMENT Interestingly, controversy surrounds the best \
   treatment approach, with some advocating a non-directive approach and others considering \
   it a "disaster." Family therapy, especially if it involves the extended family, should be used \
   when possible. Incorporating traditional healing practices is generally recommended. \
