\
Once again, older adults do not show as much impairment on real-world tasks of recall as \
they do on laboratory tests. \
\
Possible physiological explanations for the decline in memory over the lifespan include \
atrophy of the hippocampus, decreasing activity of certain neurotransmitters (including \
acetylcholine, serotonin, and the catecholamines), and the toxic effects of endogenous \
amino acids. \
