C. LEVINSON \
\
According to Levinson's Seasons of a Man's Life theory (1978), development proceeds \
through alternating periods of transition and stability. Levinson based his theory on \
interviews with 40 men who held professional jobs. This theory has been criticized both \
for excluding persons of lower socioeconomic status, and for excluding women and their \
development. In this theory, the role assigned to the woman is that of fulfilling her \
husband's dreams. Levinson proposed that when the woman is no longer needed by her \
husband and children, she can begin to form her identity. \
\
>EARLY ADULT TRANSITION During the early adult transition (17 - 22), the person \
starts to change the sense of self developed during childhood and begins to make some \
tentative choices about life as an adult. \
\
>ENTERING THE ADULT WORLD During the phase of entering the adult world (22 \
- 28), the person consolidates choices made earlier about career, social relationships, \
values, and lifestyle. \
\
>AGE 30 TRANSITION The age 30 transition (28 - 33) involves establishing patterns \
of adult life, which may include a reconsideration of choices made before. The person may \
feel as if there is little time left to establish one's life, which may make this a very stressful \
period. \
\
>SETTLING DOWN   During the settling down phase (33 - 40), the person has settled \
into commitments as an adult, often assuming more responsibilities and establishing \
routines. \
\
>MID-LIFE TRANSITION The mid-life transition (40 - 45) phase involves a change \
in perspective from "time since birth" to "time left to live." This period sometimes involves \
crises, possibly leading to significant changes (e.g., divorce, career change). \
\
>MIDDLE ADULTHOOD    During middle adulthood (45 - 50) the person begins to \
relinquish the perspective of early adulthood and may make major adjustments as a result \
of this change in perspective, including planning for the future (e.g., retirement). \
\
>AGE 50 TRANSITION Age 50 transition involves making changes associated with \
entering this decade of life. \
