than in the general population include anxiety disorders, major depressive disorder, and \
substance use disorder. Co-occurring disorders also include antisocial and other personality \
disorders, obsessive-compulsive disorder, tic disorder, and autism spectrum disorder. By \
early adulthood, ADHD is associated with an increased suicide risk, especially when \
comorbid with a mood, conduct, or substance use disorder. \
\
