 social/occupational impairment. \
\
 With mood-congruent or mood-incongruent psychotic features involves the presence of \
 delusions or hallucination at any time in the episode. Mood-congruent features involve \
 delusions and hallucinations consistent with the mood (e.g., themes of grandiosity or \
 invulnerability during a manic episode), while mood-incongruent features occur when the \
