\
 With peripartum onset is specified when the onset of the current or most recent mood \
 episode is during pregnancy or within 4 weeks of delivery. \
\
 With seasonal pattern applies when there is a regular temporal relationship between the \
 onset of a mood episode and a particular time of the year (e.g., fall or winter), and full \
