and symptoms are minimal or absent in the week postmenses. At least one of the following \
must be present: marked affective lability, marked irritability or increased interpersonal \
conflict, marked depressed mood, or marked anxiety. Additionally, at least one of the \
following must be present (to reach a total of five symptoms): decreased interest in usual \
activities, difficulty concentrating, lethargy or fatigue, change in appetite, insomnia or \
hypersomnia, feeling overwhelmed, and physical symptoms (e.g., breast tenderness, \
joint/muscle pain, bloating, or weight gain). These symptoms must be present for most \
menstrual cycles in the preceding year. \
\
>SUBSTANCE/MEDICATION-INDUCED DEPRESSIVE DISORDER Substances \
that can induce a depressive disorder include alcohol, hallucinogens (including PCP). \
inhalants, opioids, sedatives, hypnotics and anxiolyties, and stimulants (including cocaine). \
\
>DEPRESSIVE DISORDER DUE TO ANOTHER MEDICAL CONDITION \
Medical conditions that are known to manifest with symptoms of depression include stroke, \
Huntington's disease, Parkinson's disease, and traumatic brain injury. Additionally, the \
neuroendocrine conditions of hypothyroidism and Cushing's disease are associated with \
depression. \
\
>OTHER SPECIFIC/UNSPECIFIED DEPRESSIVE DISORDER Examples of other \
specified depressive disorder include short duration depressive episode (4 - 13 days), or \
depressive episode with insufficient symptoms (depressed affect with at least one of the \
other eight symptoms, for at least 2 weeks). \
