The duration of symptoms of PTSD varies widely, with complete recovery within 3 months \
occurring in 50% of individuals with PTSD. For others, symptoms last longer than 12 \
months, or sometimes more than 50 years. Risk factors for the development of PTSD \
include severity of the trauma, perceived life threat, interpersonal violence (e.g., a child \
witnessing a threat to the caregiver), prior mental disorders, dissociation during and after \
the trauma, lack of social support, female gender, younger age, lower SES, lower \
education, lower intelligence, and minority racial/ethnic status. PTSD is more prevalent \
among females than males and is associated with suicidal ideation and attempts. \
