Evidence-based interventions for PTSD include cognitive processing therapy (CPT), \
prolonged exposure (PE), seeking safety (for PTSD with co-morbid substance use \
disorder), and eye movement desensitization and reprocessing (EMDR). EMDR is \
considered an effective treatment but its efficacy is controversial, as the mechanism of \
change may simply be exposure. The eye movements or other bilateral stimulation, which \
were originally believed to be the curative factors in EMDR, have been shown to have no \
unique effects and to make no contribution to overall effectiveness. As a treatment for \
PTSD, stress inoculation therapy is considered to have modest research support. \
