The technique of psychological debriefing (PD), originally touted as a method to prevent \
the development of PTSD and other trauma-related symptoms, had been used widely after \
disasters, such as 9/11. However, the current consensus is that the method is ineffective; \
some research has even indicated that the technique makes recovery more difficult as \
compared to having no treatment at all. \
