eating followed by inappropriate compensatory behavior to prevent weight gain (e.g., \
laxatives, vomiting, enemas, fasting, or excessive exercise). These episodes occur at least \
once a week for 3 months. Binge eating is described as eating within a discrete time period \
(e.g., 2 hours) an amount definitely larger than most would, or a sense of lack of control \
over eating during the episode. \
\
As appropriate, the specifiers of in partial remission or in full should be used. Current \
severity is also specified based on the average number of episodes of inappropriate \
compensatory behaviors each week: mild (1 - 3), moderate (4 - 7), severe (8 - 13), or \
extreme (14+). \
\
