\
>ANTISOCIAL PERSONALITY DISORDER   Features of this disorder include a \
pervasive pattern of disregard for and violation of the rights of others since at least age 15, \
as indicated by three or more of the following: repeatedly committing unlawful acts; \
deceitfulness (e.g., lying, conning); impulsivity and failure to plan ahead; repeated physical \
fights/assaults; disregard for the safety of self or others; irresponsibility (e.g., failure to \
keep a job or honor financial obligations); lack of remorse. The individual must be at least \
18 years old and there is evidence of conduct disorder before age 15. \
