>BORDERLINE PERSONALITY DISORDER   The hallmark of this disorder is a \
pattern of instability of mood, interpersonal relationships, and self-image, as well as \
significant impulsivity as indicated by five or more of the following: efforts to avoid \
abandonment; intense, unstable relationships characterized by idealization and \
devaluation; unstable self-image; impulsivity in two areas that are potentially damaging \
