\
>NARCISSISTIC PERSONALITY DISORDER This disorder involves a pattern of \
grandiosity, need for admiration, and lack of empathy, as indicated by five or more of the \
following: a grandiose sense of self-importance; preoccupation with fantasies of greatness \
(e.g., power, brilliance, beauty): believes that he or she is special; needs excessive \
admiration; has a sense of entitlement; is interpersonally exploitative (e.g., uses others); \
lacks empathy; is envious of others, or thinks others are envious of him or her; is arrogant \
and haughty. \
\
Cluster C Personality Disorders: Anxious and Fearful \
\
>AVOIDANT PERSONALITY DISORDER Characteristics of avoidant personality \
disorder include a pattern of social inhibition, feelings of inadequacy, and hypersensitivity \
to negative evaluation, as evidenced by four or more of the following: avoids occupational \
activities due to fear of criticism, disapproval, or rejection; generally unwilling to get \
involved with others unless certain of being liked; restrained in intimate relationship (due \
to fear of shame or ridicule); preoccupied with concerns of rejection and criticism in social \
situations; inhibited in new situations due to a sense of inadequacy; views self as socially \
inept or inferior; reluctant to take risks or try new things because of potential \
embarrassment. \
\
