\
misidentifying innocent people in mugshots and lineups in staged crimes. Furthermore, \
people frequently report inaccurate memories with a high degree of confidence. \
\
>REPRESSED MEMORIES The area of repressed memories has stirred heated debate. \
Repressed memories include memories of traumatic events that are thought by some to \
have been completely repressed and therefore inaccessible to memory for years or even \
decades. Evidence against repressed memories comes from the finding that most people \
who have witnessed a violent crime or are victims of abuse have trouble forgetting rather \
than remembering the event. Memory experts believe that it is rare for people to first \
recover memories of early childhood abuse years after the abuse has taken place. \
Furthermore, it is possible to construct convincing false memories for events that never \
happened. \
\
\
