\
When test-takers are attempting to "fake good" on the MMPI-2, they typically have a low \
F and high K. When they are attempting to "fake bad," they typically have a high F and \
low K. \
\
The 10 clinical scales on the MMPI-2 serve as clinical/ personality indices, \
\
        SCALE 1 - HYPOCHONDRIASIS (HS) High scorers have a variety of \
       physical complaints and are illness-focused. They are commonly immature, \
       egocentric, complaining, and pessimistic. \
\
        SCALE 2 - DEPRESSION (D) This scale measures depression, general \
       dissatisfaction, and pessimism. Elevations suggest guilt, indecision, self- \
       criticism, low self-esteem, and a tendency to withdraw. \
\
        SCALE 3 - HYSTERIA (HY) High scores indicate physical complaints as \
       well as a defensive denial of emotional or interpersonal problems, demand for \
       affection and support, and social disinhibition. \
\
       SCALE 4 - PSYCHOPATHIC DEVIATE (PD) Pd measures the general \
       level of social adjustment. High scorers are frequently manipulative, hostile, \
       impulsive, have poor judgment, and have problems with authority, \
       commitments, and family. Substance use is common with elevations on Pd. \
\
        SCALE 5 - MASCULINITY-FEMININITY (MF) Male high scorers have \
       aesthetic interests and express warmth, while low scorers have traditionally \
       more masculine interests. High scoring females endorse traditionally male \
       interests and are confident and logical, while low scoring females may be \
       passive and yielding. \
\
        SCALE 6 -- PARANOIA (PA) High scorers are suspicious, resentful, angry. \
       and externalize blame. High scorers tend to misinterpret others' motives and \
       are interpersonally sensitive. \
\
        SCALE 7 - PSYCHASTHENIA (PT) High scores indicate fears, anxieties, \
       compulsions, obsessions, indecisiveness, and ruminative self-doubt. Elevations \
       suggest tension, worry, and uncertainty. Along with Scale 2, an elevation on \
       this scale is a good overall measure of distress. \
\
\
 \
\
